description:
Responsibilities
To design, develop and conduct training programmes to ensure trainees obtain adequate skills and knowledge to provide quality services to the customers including but not restricted to classroom, on-site, systems-related or e-learning operational training;
To evaluate and review the training programmes to ensure training requirements and effectiveness are met;
To train the trainers appointed by both internal and external parties including operations contractors, Cargo Agents, and Government parties;
To maintain and update all training materials in line with the latest operating procedures and instructions;
To conduct assessment on the proficiency of trainees under probation as and when required;
To ensure training records of all trainees are complete and up-to-date;
To support Quality Control and conduct inspections for improving the operations quality;
To complete special projects and other requirements assigned by supervisor.

 Requirement

F.7 or tertiary education preferably in Logistics, Aviation Management, Training and Development or related discipline.
Minimum 3 years of solid working experience in aviation industry, air cargo terminal, logistics company, warehouse or freight forwarding Company, of which minimum 2 years in providing staff training or performing supervisory duties;
Hands-on experience in the air-cargo terminal operations would be beneficial;
DG license (Cat. 6) holder is preferable;
Knowledge and experience in e-learning is an advantage;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Strong planning, organising and analytical skills;
Good interpersonal & communication skills with proactive, tactful & result-oriented personality;
Able to work independently and under pressure;
Candidate with more experience will be considered as Training Specialist 
To apply, you may email your confidential resume with date of availability, current and expected salary to recruitment @cpsl.com.hk. Applicants not contacted within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.
Cathay Pacific Services Limited is an Equal Opportunities Employer. Personal data provided by job applicants will be used strictly in accordance with our personal data policy and for recruitment purposes only. Candidates not notified within six weeks may consider their application unsuccessful. All related information will be kept in our file for up to 24 months.

About our client
A Fast-growing Global Biotechnology company, its headquarter is in Hong Kong with offices in APAC & Europe, who is seeking a NEW Team Head about Learning & People Development, reports to the Chief People Officer (Global).

Energetic, move fast and develop a lot of ideas
Corporate experience with regional exposure
Analyze & Design Training programs
Fluent English and Chinese Speaking
Comfortable with hands-on operations

Responsibilities


Oversee the company’s people development plan and support culture building roadmap;
Build up the team and function in learning and development area for the company;
Formulate strategy and drive initiatives on leadership development and performance enhancement;
Advise leadership team on functional development needs;
Strengthen the communication among all regions through establishing regular and effective channels.
Requirements
8+ years of relevant experience and recent people management experience;
Track record in building L&D function and leading culture change, experience in consulting capacity is a plus;
Rich experience in implementing L&D initiatives as facilitator and project manager;
Ability to drive projects and navigate in dynamic and regional set up, preferably hyper-speed growth environment;
Proactive and highly tactful in stakeholder management;
Excellent presentation and audience engagement skills;
High proficiency in speaking and writing Chinese and English;
Comfortable with hands-on tasks and fast-paced working environment.
To apply, please click on the ‘Apply Now’ button or contact Nick Chow at (852) 3502-2637 for a confidential discussion. Alternatively, email your resume (with your notice period, current and expected salary) to nick.chow@macleansgroup .com

Your interest will be treated in strict confidence and only shortlisted candidates will be notified.

Responsibilities:

Provide full spectrum of human resources support including but not limited to recruitment, payroll administration, compensation and benefits, performance management, training and staff relations;
Able to manage monthly payroll, final payment and related calculation via system independently;
Assist in reviewing and formulating HR policies and procedures;
Ensure compliance with employment and related legislations;
Prepare and maintain documentation and reports from staff onboarding to offboarding; and
Opportunities to participate in ad hoc projects as assigned.

Requirements:

Diploma or Degree holder in Human Resources or related disciplines;
Minimum 4-5 years’ relevant experience with exposure in NGO will be an advantage but not a must;
Well-versed in Hong Kong Employment Ordinance;
Detail-minded, self-motivated and demonstrates ability to work independently and contributes as a strong team player;
Excellent problem-solving, communication and organizational skills;
Excellent command of both spoken and written English and Chinese;
Proficiency in MS Word, Excel and Chinese word processing;
Immediate available is preferred;
Candidate with more experience may be considered for a more senior role

Staff Benefits:

Regular Sunday and Public Holidays off
14 to 18 days’ annual leave entitlement
Medical benefits to staff and dependent
On-the-job training and training sponsorship & study leave

Interested parties please send full resume with last and expected salary to Human Resources Unit, United Christian Nethersole Community Health Service, L1, KEC Administrative Building, No. 2 Po Ning Lane, Hang Hau, Tseung Kwan O with job reference no. marked on the envelope or by clicking "Apply Now"

(Applicants not invited for interview within 4 weeks from the closing date may consider their applications unsuccessful. All personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and will only be used for recruitment related purpose.)

Responsibilities

Support the implementation of “5-S” management system and perform on-site audit in restaurants;
Maintain environmental, health & safety record and documents;
Follow up work injury case and prepare related reports and documents;
Organize the occupational safety training and modify & update the training materials from time to time;
Ensure the operations in restaurants are in compliance with safety regulations and corporate requirements;
Perform ad-hoc duties as assigned

Requirements:

Diploma holder or above in related disciplines;
A minimum of 1 year’s working experience in clerical support, recent graduates will be also considered;
Experience in F&B operations and restaurant group is preferable;
Knowledge in Safety and Health Ordinance is an advantage;
Strong presentation and communications skills;
Good inter-personal skills & able to work independently;
Good written and spoken English and Chinese;
Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Excel, and PowerPoint
Working Location : Fotan



We offer competitive package and benefits:

         Five-Day work week
         3 Days Marriage Leave
         5 Days Full Pay Paternity Leave
         Family-Friendly Leave
         Birthday Leave
         Free Duty Meal
         Staff Discount
         Medical Allowance
         Insurance Plan
         Promotion Opportunities

For more company information, please visit our web site at www.taihing.com

Interested parties please send full resume with expected salary and availability to the Human Resources Department via email.

All information received will be kept in strict confidence and only used for employment-related purposes. Applicants who are not invited for interview within 6 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.

Responsibilities:

Identify company training needs, formulate and develop training strategies and implement plans for all frontline staff;
Manage training budget, course development, training need analysis and program review
Design rundown, prepare training hand-outs, materials, tools and samples before training classes;
Deliver customer service, selling skills and supervisory training to front-line staff;
Execute field work in shops to evaluate front-line staff’s performance;
Conduct Train The Trainer sessions and provide coaching and development when appropriate.

Requirements:

Bachelor Degree in Human Resources Management, Training or related disciplines;
Minimum 8 years of solid experience in training and development especially in F&B industry;
Self-motivated, well organized and a good team player;
Strong communication, presentation and interpersonal skills;
Proficiency in using MS Office applications including Word, PowerPoint, Excel and Chinese Word Processing;
Candidates with more experience will be considered as Senior Operations Training Manager

We offer 5-day work week, on-the-job development program and rewarding career opportunities for ambitious individuals who are looking for challenges.

(All personal data collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.)

Scope of Duties: 

Work collaboratively and in strong partnership with Learning and Development Manager/ Line Managers/ Local HR to drive HAECO Group talent management initiatives, e.g. succession planning;
Lead and manage the talent management team;
Manage and support the development and delivery of talent initiatives;
Nurture the High Flyers within the relevant business area and use existing talent frameworks to support their growth;
Leverage data from SuccessFactors to provide insights and help inform decisions;
Identify and develop competency assessment models for talent development;
Perform other relevant duties as assigned

Requirements: 

Degree in Training & Development, Human Resources Management or related discipline;
5 years of relevant experience in a sizable organization;
Advanced project management skills, data savvy, and strong systems thinking and understanding;
Proficiency in MS Office applications e.g. PowerPoint, Excel, and Chinese Word Processing
Strong supervisory skills and analytical abilities;
Good team player and people skills to develop rapport with line managers and all levels of employees;
Positive attitude and able to deal with multi-tasks effectively;
Excellent command of English and Chinese, both spoken and written. Fluency in Putonghua

How to Apply:

Please send your resume with expected salary, quoting the employer's reference no., to: Human Resources Department - Resourcing Team, Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Company Limited, 80 South Perimeter Road, Hong Kong International Airport, Lantau, Hong Kong OR submit your application via https://careers.haeco.com/hkg/job-openings/

Candidates not contacted 4-6 weeks after submission of applications and/or interviews may consider their application unsuccessful.

All information provided by candidates will be treated in strict confidence and will be used for employment purpose only.

We are a well-established Building Services Contractor.  To cope with our rapid business development, we are now looking for high caliber talents to join our company.



 Job Responsibilities:

Assist in all-rounded human resources functions, including staff recruitment, compensation & benefits administration, staff relations, performance management, training and development;
Participate in  annual HR exercises and ad-hoc tasks as assigned.
Job Requirements:

Diploma or above in Human Resources Management or equivalent;
1-2 years of relevant HR experience;
Well versed in Hong Kong Employment Ordinance and other HR related ordinances;
Self-driven, well-organized and detail-minded;
Good interpersonal and communication skills;
Strong computer literacy in MS Office, with HRIS experience is preferred;
Candidate with less experience will be considered as Human Resources Assistant.
Fresh graduates are welcomed.

Interested parties, please apply with full resume, date availability, current and expected salary to the Human Resources Manager by clicking "Apply Now".

To learn more about us, please visit our website: aster.hk.com 

We are an equal-opportunity employer and welcome applications from all qualified candidates. Personal data collected will be treated in strict confidence and will be used for recruitment purpose only.  Applicants who are not invited for an interview within 8 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful.

Scope of Duties: 

Work closely with Assistant Manager, Group Talent Management;  
Engage in talent review, succession planning and performance management exercises across all HAECO Group entities; 
Manage the talent management programmes for the Group;  
Administer and maintain the Performance Management and Succession Planning systems; 
Provide regular tracking reports and relevant analysis. 
Liaise and negotiate with internal and external parties on talent development related activities;  
Perform other relevant duties as assigned 

Requirements: 

Holder of recognised degree in Human Resources or related disciplines;  
3 years of solid experience in talent management or human resources functions at sizable organisations;  
Attention to details, action-oriented and a good team player;  
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills;  
Hands-on experience in SAP/ HR systems is preferred; 
Proficiency in MS Office applications e.g. Word, PowerPoint and Excel 
Excellent command of English and Chinese, both spoken and written, fluency in Putonghua will be an advantage 

How to Apply:

Please send your resume with expected salary, quoting the employer's reference no., to: Human Resources Department - Talent & Partnership Team, Hong Kong Aircraft Engineering Company Limited, 80 South Perimeter Road, Hong Kong International Airport, Lantau, Hong Kong OR submit your application via https://careers.haeco.com/hkg/job-openings/

Candidates not contacted 4-6 weeks after submission of applications and/or interviews may consider their application unsuccessful.

All information provided by candidates will be treated in strict confidence and will be used for employment purpose only.

Working in Tao Heung Group, besides remuneration and benefits, you can also
1) Get a chance to work in one of the largest F&B groups,
2) Get cross-border exposure, and
3) Get some challenging yet fulfilling and rewarding experience.

Please join us as:

Training Officer

Job Description:

Assist in training programs for all front-line staff levels to enhance and polish customer services skill, product knowledge, and drive the Company culture;
Coordinate with different parties for training implementation;
Maintain and update training materials and record, prepare training statistics in regular basis;
Provide logistic support and participate in other projects as required.

Requirement:

Degree in Human Resources Management, Training or related discipline;
2 years solid experience in training and development, preferably in F&B industry;
Experience in Mystery Shopper and QF programs would be an advantage;
High attention to details, good communication and interpersonal skills;
Independent, fast-paced, multi-tasking, result-oriented and self-motivated.

Interested parties please apply with detailed resume, current salary, expected salary and contact numbers to the Human Resources Manager, Tao Heung Group Ltd. by clicking "APPLY NOW"

Application letters collected will be used for recruitment purpose only.
